    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-14T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/8–1246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>, at Paris</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-14T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 14, 1946—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4082. <gloss target="#t_Secdel1">Secdel</gloss> 666. For the Secretary. Greek
                    Govt has requested Allied Mission Observance Greek Electoral Lists remain in
                    Greece to observe voting plebiscite scheduled September 1. Dept feels late date
                    invitation and impossibility adequate observation with present staff make
                    advisability negative reply to Greek invitation. Please advise Dept your
                    decision urgently as Mission now in Athens recommends reply be made to Greece
                    before publication its report on condition electoral lists now expected ready
                    for release to press Saturday Aug 17.<note n="50" xml:id="d134fn50">The
                        Secretary of State, in telegram <gloss target="#t_Delsec1">Delsec</gloss>
                        824 (No. 4054) from Paris, August 16, 1946, 1 p.m., replied as follows:
                        “Unless you feel that it is entirely impracticable to accept Greek
                        invitation to observe voting on plebiscite, I should like to comply with
                        request.” (740.00119 Council/8–1646)</note> Or you may wish to communicate
                    direct with Tsaldaris and Brit in Paris.</p>
                <p>Sent Paris 4082; rptd London 6028, Athens 1001.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
